# Skill Placement Rules (Core Foundation §21)

Before implementing any **skill**, determine the layer. **Pause** until placement is approved.

| Layer | Purpose | Paths |
|-------|---------|-------|
| **Platform** | Global governance, rollouts, metrics | `app/platform/skills/`, `components/platform/skills/` |
| **Customer App** | Installed skills, settings, activity | `app/app/skills/`, `components/app/skills/` |
| **Embedded** | Runtime in customer environments | `app/api/embed/`, `app/api/install/`, `components/embed/` |

## Workflow (`lib/core/skills.ts`)

Define → Layer → Permissions → Approval → Implement → Internal validation → Unonight pilot → Public release

Register in `lib/core/skills/registry.ts` before shipping. See [SKILL_ENGINE.md](../../SKILL_ENGINE.md) and [CORE_FOUNDATION.md §21](../../CORE_FOUNDATION.md#21-skill-placement-rules).

Never place skills in existing folders out of convenience.
